<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/37888786-pauline"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/37888786-pauline">Pauline </a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Compared to a lot of the books marketed towards kids that age, I think this is much cleaner. Yes, there are details about gender selection but there i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Compared to a lot of the books marketed towards kids that age, I think this is much cleaner. Yes, there are details about gender selection but there is no graphic content of any kind. I would allow my 12 year old to read it. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
