<div id="review_90018914" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/90018914" />
    <a title="Teresa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3299846-teresa"><img alt="Teresa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1491778070p2/3299846.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/90018914?book_show_action=true">Feb 16, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Teresa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Teresa" href="/user/show/3299846-teresa">Teresa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3299846-teresa?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer90018914" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7914962922308052223">This is an extremely well crafted story. The characters are multi-faceted and they and their relationships grow throughout the book. I am amazed at how nimbly the author is able to jump back and forth between Mumbai and California, and even make a few jumps in time. Secret Daughter is a smooth, compelling and wholesome read. And if you wonder how it is going to end, or think you know how it SHOULD end, just trust the author, because it is obvious Shilpi Somaya Gowda knows what she is doing. This</span>
  <span id="freeText7914962922308052223" style="display:none">This is an extremely well crafted story. The characters are multi-faceted and they and their relationships grow throughout the book. I am amazed at how nimbly the author is able to jump back and forth between Mumbai and California, and even make a few jumps in time. Secret Daughter is a smooth, compelling and wholesome read. And if you wonder how it is going to end, or think you know how it SHOULD end, just trust the author, because it is obvious Shilpi Somaya Gowda knows what she is doing. This is a fabulous debut novel; I can't wait to read more from Shilpi in the future!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7914962922308052223" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


